## Roster: Plucked Family

Let's define several plucked instruments and hear the differences.

### Guitar

```scheme
(define-instrument 'acoustic-guitar
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.4 0.25 0.15))
  (adsr :a 0.008 :d 0.35 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2200 :q 1.2)
  (add-formant 220 '(400 900)))

(part (voice 'acoustic-guitar)
  '((330 0.5) (370 0.5) (392 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, add-formant]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, formant bank -->

### Harp

```scheme
(define-instrument 'concert-harp
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.3 0.2 0.1))
  (adsr :a 0.003 :d 0.5 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 3500 :q 0.6))

(part (voice 'concert-harp)
  '((523 0.4) (587 0.4) (659 0.4) (698 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Harpsichord

```scheme
(define-instrument 'harpsichord
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.8 0.6 0.4))
  (adsr :a 0.002 :d 0.15 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'highpass :cutoff 800 :q 0.5))

(part (voice 'harpsichord)
  '((294 0.25) (330 0.25) (370 0.25) (392 0.3)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Kalimba

```scheme
(define-instrument 'kalimba
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.4 0.15))
  (adsr :a 0.005 :d 0.6 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (add-formant 440 '(1200 2400)))

(part (voice 'kalimba)
  '((523 0.35) (659 0.35) (784 0.35) (880 0.4)))
```

*[needs: adsr, add-formant]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, formant bank -->

Each plucked voice has zero sustain (`:s 0.0`)—the note dies after the decay. But decay time, filter cutoff, and harmonic content vary, giving each its character.

---

## Roster: Bowed Family

Bowed instruments sustain. The envelope has a high sustain level and a slow attack.

### Violin

```scheme
(define-instrument 'solo-violin
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.9 0.7 0.5 0.4 0.3))
  (noise 'white :level 0.03)
  (adsr :a 0.12 :d 0.08 :s 0.8 :r 0.2)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2800 :q 1.8))

(part (voice 'solo-violin)
  '((440 0.8) (494 0.8) (523 0.9)))
```

*[needs: noise, adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise generator, adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Cello

```scheme
(define-instrument 'solo-cello
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.8 0.6 0.4 0.3))
  (adsr :a 0.18 :d 0.1 :s 0.75 :r 0.3)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1500 :q 2.2))

(part (voice 'solo-cello)
  '((220 1.0) (247 1.0) (262 1.2)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Synth Pad

```scheme
(define-instrument 'warm-pad
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.33 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.3 :d 0.2 :s 0.9 :r 0.5)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1200 :q 0.8))

(part (voice 'warm-pad)
  '((330 1.5) (392 1.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

Pads have very slow attacks (0.3s) and long releases—they swell and fade.

---

## Roster: Blown Family

Blown instruments mix tone with breath noise. The filter is often a bandpass, and the envelope has a moderate attack.

### Wooden Flute

```scheme
(define-instrument 'wood-flute
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.3 0.15))
  (noise 'white :level 0.06)
  (adsr :a 0.09 :d 0.05 :s 0.75 :r 0.12)
  (filter 'bandpass :cutoff 1600 :q 4.0))

(part (voice 'wood-flute)
  '((523 0.6) (587 0.6) (659 0.7)))
```

*[needs: noise, adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise generator, adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Clarinet

```scheme
(define-instrument 'clarinet
  (wave 'square)
  (partials '(1.0 0.0 0.3 0.0 0.15))
  (noise 'white :level 0.04)
  (adsr :a 0.07 :d 0.05 :s 0.8 :r 0.15)
  (filter 'bandpass :cutoff 1200 :q 5.0))

(part (voice 'clarinet)
  '((392 0.7) (440 0.7) (494 0.8)))
```

*[needs: noise, adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise generator, adsr envelope, filter verb -->

Clarinets emphasize odd harmonics (square wave base), with a narrow bandpass.

### Pan Pipes

```scheme
(define-instrument 'pan-pipes
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.2))
  (noise 'white :level 0.08)
  (adsr :a 0.05 :d 0.03 :s 0.7 :r 0.1)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.5))

(part (voice 'pan-pipes)
  '((659 0.5) (698 0.5) (784 0.6)))
```

*[needs: noise, adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise generator, adsr envelope, filter verb -->

More breath noise, fewer harmonics—airier.

---

## Roster: Struck Family

Struck instruments have very short attacks and often include inharmonic partials (bells, glockenspiel) or rich, decaying spectra (piano, marimba).

### Piano

```scheme
(define-instrument 'upright-piano
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.4 0.25 0.15 0.1))
  (adsr :a 0.003 :d 0.4 :s 0.2 :r 0.3)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 3000 :q 0.9))

(part (voice 'upright-piano)
  '((262 0.5) (330 0.5) (392 0.6)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Marimba

```scheme
(define-instrument 'wood-marimba
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.4 0.2 0.1))
  (adsr :a 0.002 :d 0.2 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (add-formant 440 '(800 1600)))

(part (voice 'wood-marimba)
  '((330 0.4) (392 0.4) (440 0.4) (494 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, add-formant]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, formant bank -->

### Glockenspiel

```scheme
(define-instrument 'glockenspiel
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.8 0.5 0.3))
  (adsr :a 0.001 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'highpass :cutoff 1500 :q 0.7))

(part (voice 'glockenspiel)
  '((1047 0.3) (1175 0.3) (1319 0.3) (1397 0.4)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

Glockenspiels are bright (high cutoff, highpass filter) and ring briefly.

### Tubular Bell

```scheme
(define-instrument 'tubular-bell
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.56 0.92 0.51 0.67))
  (adsr :a 0.005 :d 1.5 :s 0.0 :r 0.0))

(part (voice 'tubular-bell)
  '((523 1.8)))
```

*[needs: adsr]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope -->

Inharmonic partials (the ratios aren't integer multiples) give bells their distinctive clang.

---

## Roster: Electronic Family

Pure synthesis—no attempt to model an acoustic instrument.

### Square Lead

```scheme
(define-instrument 'square-lead
  (wave 'square)
  (partials '(1.0 0.0 0.33 0.0 0.2))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.1 :s 0.5 :r 0.1)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1800 :q 1.5))

(part (voice 'square-lead)
  '((440 0.4) (494 0.4) (523 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Sawtooth Bass

```scheme
(define-instrument 'saw-bass
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.8 0.6 0.5))
  (adsr :a 0.008 :d 0.08 :s 0.4 :r 0.08)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 350 :q 3.0))

(part (voice 'saw-bass)
  '((110 0.6) (123 0.6) (131 0.7)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

High Q (3.0) makes the filter resonant—classic acid bass sound.

### Sine Lead

```scheme
(define-instrument 'sine-lead
  (wave 'sine)
  (adsr :a 0.02 :d 0.05 :s 0.6 :r 0.15))

(part (voice 'sine-lead)
  '((659 0.4) (698 0.4) (784 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope -->

Pure sine, no harmonics—clean, minimal.

