## Modding in Practice: One Voice, Many Flavors

Let's take a single base voice and mod it several ways to show the range.

### Base: Generic Pluck

```scheme
(define-instrument 'generic-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.0))

(part (voice 'generic-pluck)
  '((440 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

### Mod: Dark (Low Cutoff)

```scheme
(define-instrument 'generic-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'dark-pluck
  (mod-instrument 'generic-pluck
    :cutoff 800))

(part (voice 'dark-pluck)
  '((440 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, mod-instrument]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, mod-instrument macro -->

### Mod: Metallic (High Q)

```scheme
(define-instrument 'generic-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'metal-pluck
  (mod-instrument 'generic-pluck
    :q 4.0))

(part (voice 'metal-pluck)
  '((440 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, mod-instrument]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, mod-instrument macro -->

### Mod: Soft (Fewer Harmonics, Low Q)

```scheme
(define-instrument 'generic-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'soft-pluck
  (mod-instrument 'generic-pluck
    :partials '(1.0 0.3)
    :q 0.5))

(part (voice 'soft-pluck)
  '((440 0.5)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, mod-instrument]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, mod-instrument macro -->

### Mod: Short (Fast Decay)

```scheme
(define-instrument 'generic-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2000 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'short-pluck
  (mod-instrument 'generic-pluck
    :d 0.08))

(part (voice 'short-pluck)
  '((440 0.3)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, mod-instrument]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, mod-instrument macro -->

Five flavors from one base. Each mod changes one or two parameters; everything else inherits.

