## Swapping Voices Mid-Phrase

You can play different sections of a phrase through different voices by splitting the phrase into parts.

```scheme
(define-instrument 'harp-pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.3 0.15))
  (adsr :a 0.005 :d 0.4 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 3000 :q 0.7))

(define-instrument 'cello-bow
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.2))
  (adsr :a 0.2 :d 0.1 :s 0.7 :r 0.3)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1200 :q 2.0))

(part (voice 'harp-pluck)
  '((440 0.4) (494 0.4)))

(part (voice 'cello-bow)
  '((523 0.8) (587 0.8)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

First two notes are harp, next two are cello. Same melody, different timbres mid-stream.

---

## Building a Mod Chain

You can mod a mod—apply deltas on top of deltas.

```scheme
(define-instrument 'base-saw
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.7 0.5))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.2 :s 0.3 :r 0.1)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1500 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'bright-saw
  (mod-instrument 'base-saw
    :cutoff 2500))

(define-instrument 'bright-long-saw
  (mod-instrument 'bright-saw
    :d 0.5
    :r 0.3))

(part (voice 'bright-long-saw)
  '((220 0.8)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter, mod-instrument]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb, mod-instrument macro -->

`bright-saw` inherits from `base-saw` and raises the cutoff. `bright-long-saw` inherits from `bright-saw` and lengthens the decay and release. Each mod builds on the previous.

---

## Family Tour: A Progression Through Families

Let's play a simple chord progression, changing the voice family on each chord.

```scheme
(define-instrument 'pluck
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2200 :q 1.0))

(define-instrument 'pad
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.33))
  (adsr :a 0.2 :d 0.0 :s 1.0 :r 0.4))

(define-instrument 'bell
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.5 0.3))
  (adsr :a 0.003 :d 0.7 :s 0.0 :r 0.0))

(part (voice 'pluck)
  '((330 0.5) (392 0.5) (440 0.5)))

(part (voice 'pad)
  '((349 1.2) (415 1.2)))

(part (voice 'bell)
  '((370 0.6) (440 0.6) (523 0.7)))
```

*[needs: adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope, filter verb -->

Three families, three timbres, one progression.

---

## Layering Voices

You can play the *same* notes through *multiple* voices at once—layering.

```scheme
(define-instrument 'soft-pad
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.3))
  (adsr :a 0.3 :d 0.0 :s 1.0 :r 0.5))

(define-instrument 'bell-layer
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.5 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.005 :d 0.6 :s 0.0 :r 0.0))

(define melody '((440 1.0) (494 1.0) (523 1.2)))

(part (voice 'soft-pad) melody)
(part (voice 'bell-layer) melody)
```

*[needs: adsr]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr envelope -->

Both voices play the same notes. The pad sustains, the bell rings and decays. The combination creates a richer texture.

---

## Roster Snapshot: Quick Reference

Here's a compact roster you might keep on hand—one voice per family, ready to call.

```scheme
(define-instrument 'guitar
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.4 0.25))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.3 :s 0.0 :r 0.0)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2200 :q 1.2))

(define-instrument 'violin
  (wave 'sawtooth)
  (partials '(1.0 0.8 0.6 0.4))
  (adsr :a 0.15 :d 0.1 :s 0.75 :r 0.25)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2500 :q 1.5))

(define-instrument 'flute
  (wave 'sine)
  (partials '(1.0 0.3))
  (noise 'white :level 0.05)
  (adsr :a 0.08 :d 0.05 :s 0.8 :r 0.15)
  (filter 'bandpass :cutoff 1800 :q 3.0))

(define-instrument 'piano
  (wave 'triangle)
  (partials '(1.0 0.6 0.4 0.25 0.15))
  (adsr :a 0.003 :d 0.4 :s 0.2 :r 0.3)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 3000 :q 0.9))

(define-instrument 'synth-lead
  (wave 'square)
  (partials '(1.0 0.0 0.33 0.0 0.2))
  (adsr :a 0.01 :d 0.1 :s 0.5 :r 0.1)
  (filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1800 :q 1.5))
```

*[needs: noise, adsr, filter]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise generator, adsr envelope, filter verb -->

